 introduction and translations, this new edition contains Michelangelo’s original Italian poetry, a chronology of his life and works, a biographical profile of Tusiani, and an interview with Tusiani exploring his musings on classic literature and the subtle art of translation. The Complete Poems of Michelangelo sheds light on Tusiani’s many exceptional accomplishments during his long and prolific life as a scholar, poet, translator, and artist.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOETRY / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aAnthony J. Tamburri.  aFlorence.  aItalian Renaissance.  aItalian history.  aItalian literature.  aJoseph Tusiani.  aMichelangelo Buonarroti.  acomplete works.  afacing page translation.  apoetry in translation.  apoetry.1 aRizzo, Gianluca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRizzo, Gianluca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTamburri, Anthony Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTusiani, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107671550 cprintz978148754361740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754364840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487543648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487543648/original  